  <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'> What is Tax? </h3>
  </div>
<p>
<strong>Tax</strong> is a compulsory payment imposed on an individual or legal entity by government to raise money for
 government expenditures e.g. income tax such as, PAYE (<strong>pay-as-you-earn</strong>).
</p>
<p>
For any salary earner or wage earner, it is not the total income that is taxable;
<br>
<strong> Taxable income </strong> = total income – allowances.
</p>
<p>
<strong>The allowances are;</strong> personal allowance, child allowance, dependent relative allowance etc. 
The accurate conditions for 
calculating the tax would be given per income earner and it varies.
</p>
